{
  "doc_id": "prion_0316",
  "text": "A 44 year old female presented with a progressive cerebellar disturbance approximately 13 years after receiving human pituitary derived gonadotrophin injections as a treatment for infertility.\nThe patient died approximately nine months later.\nCreutzfeldt-Jakob disease was confirmed at necropsy.\nThis is the second reported case of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease in a recipient of human derived gonadotrophin.",
